in the game for 12 hours <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>after</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> someone had gone to bed out of frustration.)  When you try and restart EQ again, everything will work as normal.  If you try and start a character on another server, you will get error 1120 or 1121 stating you have an active Character on another server.  When you try and log on your regular server, you won't get an error 1018, in fact you will be able to get to the Character selection screen, but as soon as you select a character your game will hang.<br><br>I am posting this here because I could think of no better place to see if this doesn't just happen to wizards.  As it stands I have to log on an alt and /petition to get a GM to restore an older back-up copy of my character and lose any items (and exp /cry) I got in the past couple days.<br><br>Please, if you've experienced this problem in the last couple weeks or so, state what you may think to be the cause, if you know any people who have had this problem, or ways you've gone to resolve this.<br><br><br>&lt;==EDIT==&gt; Removed sig.  Wow. 15k? ouch.  Makes sense though, a lot of traffic here.<br><br>Xarinthus Nihilflare Wizzynuker of the 57th Degree Burns - Quellious Server<br>Norrath Fellowship <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxarinthus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xarinthus</A> at: 3/18/02 11:56:18 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nenjindarkeyes>Nenjin Darkeyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 12:01:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22871.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Serious Character Datafile corruption! WARNING!</sp